Package: treecolorize
Type: Package
Title: Keyword-Based Coloring of Phylogenetic Trees
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("KamikiRitsu", email = "kamikiritsu510@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Colorize phylogenetic trees by taxonomic or functional group using
    simple keyword rules. Supports both ape and ggtree backends. Features include
    automatic tip-label classification via user-defined regex keyword maps,
    branch coloring by descendant majority vote, and a flexible color palette
    system. Designed for multi-kingdom datasets where quick visual grouping of
    diverse lineages is needed.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
